subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Aceria lactucae
(Canestrini, 1893), but can be differentiated from the latter by female genital coverflap with 16 ridges (female genital coverflap with 12 ridges in 
Aceria lactucae
), empodium 4-rayed (empodium 5-rayed in 
Aceria lactucae
), between median and admedian lines with short lines on prodorsal shield (between median and admedian lines smooth in 
Aceria lactucae
).
